[SN]TITLE[SN]
Belfast: Section of Malone Road closed amid subsidence fears

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A section of the Malone Road in Belfast remains closed to traffic after a small hole was discovered in the tarmac, leading to fears of subsidence.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Police were called to the scene on Sunday.
The road is shut between Eglantine Avenue and Wellington Park as an investigation gets under way to assess the damage.
The road is a main thoroughfare in the city. Diversions are in place.
